14/03/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The ruling Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP) announced on Tuesday (March 13th) that it would support sending more peacekeeping forces to Afghanistan if three conditions are met. 
First, all necessary military equipment, including vehicles, must be secured in advance. 
Secondly, the peacekeepers should receive at least two months of training before being deployed, and thirdly, the Defence Ministry must prepare a clear strategy for participation in peacekeeping missions abroad. 
Bulgaria is expected to send an additional 200 troops to help guard the airport at Kandahar. 
(Sega, 24 Chasa, Dnevnik - 14/03/07; News.bg, bTV - 13/03/07)
